        <num>CC 2530</num>
        <heading>2530.  Defect must exist before delivery</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2530.  Defect must exist before delivery
The warranty against redhibitory defects covers only defects that exist at the time of delivery.  The defect shall be presumed to have existed at the time of delivery if it appears within three days from that time.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109581</p>
